# MEASURES OF DISPERSION  

## Variance

### Formula
-  Variance σ² = Σ(x − μ)² / N

#### Questions

- Suppose the marks of students are: 
10, 12, 14 
Step 1 – Find Mean 
Mean = (10 + 12 + 14) / 3 Mean = 12 
 
Step 2 – Calculate deviation from mean 
| Value |	Deviation (x − mean) | 	Square |
|-------|----------------------|---------|
| 10 | -2 |	4 |
| 12 |	0 |	0 |
| 14 |	2 |	4 |
 
Step 3 – Variance 
Variance = (4 + 0 + 4) / 3 
Variance = 2.67 

---

## Standard Deviation 

### Formula
S.D = σ = √[ Σ(x − μ)² / N ]
Or 
S.D = σ = √Variance

#### Questions 

- Using the previous dataset: 
10, 12, 14 
Variance = 2.67 
Standard Deviation 
𝑆𝐷 = √2.67
𝑆𝐷 = ≈ 1.63 

##### Example: Stock Market 
Investors analyze stock price volatility. 
Stock A price change: 2%, 3%, 2.5%, 3% 
Stock B price change: -5%, +10%, -3%, +12% 

- Stock A
Mean = (2 + 3 + 2.5 + 3) / 4
Mean = 2.6

| Value |	Deviation (x − mean) | 	Square |
|-------|----------------------|---------|
| 2 | -0.6 | 0.36 |
| 3 | 0.4 | 0.16 |
| 2.5 | -0.1 | 0.01 |
| 3 | 0.4 | o.16 |

Variance = (0.36 + 0.16 + 0.01 + 0.16) / 4 
Variance = 0.69 / 4
Variance = 0.1725

S.D = √0.1725
S.D = 0.4153

- Stock B
Mean = (-5 + 10 + -3 + 12) / 4
Mean = 3.5

| Value |	Deviation (x − mean) | 	Square |
|-------|----------------------|---------|
| -5 | -8.5 | 72.25 |
| 10 | 6.5 | 42.25 |
| -3 | -6.5 | 42.25 |
| 12 | 8.5 | 72.25 |

Variance = 229 / 4
Variance = 57.25

S.D = √57.25
S.D = 7.566

•	Stock A → Low standard deviation → Stable stock 
•	Stock B → High standard deviation → Risky stock So investors 

